This release adds some more funcs to the golang API to make it easier to use.

There are no changes to the CLI.

name: v1.19.0 - Add support for colourised output
v1.18.0 - Add support for output formatting
body: This release adds support for output formatting via the `--format` flag.
Allow the use of any index (`[*]`) and dynamic (`(key=val)`) selectors on maps.

name: v1.7.0 - Read + Write parsers
body: Add support for different input/output data formats.

name: v1.5.1 - Fix an issue that would sometimes stop new values being saved as expected

body:
- Add support for YAML multi-document files.

This breaks the backward compatibility of `parser.Write`, but that's within an internal package so doesn't matter.

name: v1.1.0 - Add sub-selector support in dynamic selectors
body: This allows you to use nested dasel selectors in the "key" of a dynamic selector.

name: v1.0.3 - Format select output as expected
body:
This changes the output of `dasel select` which is some ways is breaking, but the existing functionality was considered a bug so it's getting fixed.

This is being released as a bug fix since dasel is 1 day old and the effects of this breaking change will be extremely minor.

name: v1.0.1 - Add XML support and simplify CLI tool
body: Add XML support and add ease of use default to the cli.
Add ability to pipe data in/out of dasel and add ability to create new elements via the `put` command.
